data.event: Twenty-three Boy Scout and Cub Scout units from throughout Northeast Nebraska's Diamond Dick District will help fight hunger in "Scouting for Food 2009" scheduled for Saturday, April 4.

- Other units from Northeast Nebraska helping this year includes Pack 136 of Madison; Pack 162 of Plainview; Pack 170 of Thurston; Troop 172 of Wakefield; Pack 176 of Laurel; and Troop 208 of Coleridge.
